s vigilantism in the Old West and the CIA’s actions in the wake of 9/11. Entertaining and thought-provoking, Rule Breaking and Political Imagination will prompt a reassessment of the nature of institutions and remind us of the critical role of political mavericks.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aFilibusters (Political science) 0aFilibusters (Political science). 0aParliamentary practice. 0aPolitical science. 0aPolitics, Practical. 0aRules (Philosophy)xPolitical aspects. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  aimagination.  ainstitutions.  apolitician.  arule-breaking.  arules.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311071193640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226473352423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780226473352.jpg  a978-3-11-071193-6  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles